4. In the VI editor, how do you search and replace an exact word pattern?
Example text: good morning goodmorning good & Write a command so that only the exact word good is replaced, and goodmorning should not be affected.
-	Step 1: Open vi editor of the file
-	Step 2: Now we have to write
Syntax: %s/\<exact-pattern\>/replace-pattern/g [We have use \< \> in search pattern to lock the boundary. ]
-	ex: %s/\<good\>/GOOD/g
 

 



